If you don't want to use a real implementation of a service, it's easier to
just register one of these "dummy" stubs in its place.

That way when somebody requests the Event service, for example, they don't
get a missing service error - they just get a no-op.

Using a stub as a service:

in the __construct()

    $this->eventService = container()->get('event');

In a method which needs to call a method on the service

    $this->eventService->trigger('load.model');
